Former Free State head of Agriculture, Peter Thabethe, is on the stand again. Editor's note: Livestream courtesy DStv 403, you can also watch it on DStv Now. JOHANNESBURG - The State Capture Commission of Inquiry is scheduled to hear more testimony on the controversial Vrede dairy farm project on Monday. Former Free State head of Agriculture, Peter Thabethe, will take the stand again. WATCH: Zondo Commission focuses on Vrede dairy farm project The commission previously heard the project was used to channel more than R200-million to Gupta-linked companies. This was money that was meant to benefit emerging farmers.